<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Holland May Nix Minn. Offer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- The men's athletic director for the  
University of Minnesota said he will consider other replacements 
for basketball coach Clem Haskins after leading candidate Terry 
Holland announced he was leaning against taking the job. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Dienhart said he talked Sunday with Holland, the University  
of Virginia's athletic director, and that Holland assured him of 
his continued interest in the position. 
</P>
<P>
	``We both concluded, however, that as he continues to evaluate  
the possibility of returning to the coaching profession, that I 
needed to move ahead with our search process,'' Dienhart said. 
</P>
<P>
	``As a result, I will continue to identify and interview other  
potential candidates for the position.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Holland said he hopes the Golden Gophers find someone else to  
take over their program, The Daily Progress reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm intrigued ... but I see nothing that says this is what  
Terry Holland should do,'' Holland told the newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd say it's a long shot that I'd leave, but I'm not going to  
flat out tell them no,'' he said. ``But I do hope they find 
somebody else.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Holland was in Greensboro, N.C., for Atlantic Coast Conference  
meetings and did not return a phone message left at his room 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	He has been the Cavaliers' athletic director since 1995 and has  
been offered a seven-year contract worth up to $1 million a year by 
Minnesota. But he said he has been working with Virginia on a new 
five-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Holland makes about $250,000 annually and said he hasn't used  
Minnesota's pursuit as a bargaining chip with Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
	Holland has a 326-173 coaching record in 16 seasons at Virginia.  
He is the school leader in career victories, last coaching in the 
1989-90 season. 
</P>
<P>
	He said the timing of the offer has been a major issue. The  
Golden Gophers are to tour Europe next month. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll be honest, if this was May, I would be more interested,''  
he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 57-year-old athletic director said he would prefer having a  
few months to review tapes of the team before being thrust back 
into coaching. 
</P>
<P>
	Holland said he could change his mind under certain  
circumstances. 
</P>
<P>
	``If somebody I wanted called and said they wanted to be my  
assistant coach, that this is an overwhelming opportunity, then I 
might see that as a sign,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Gophers are at the scholarship limit for next season,  
meaning the new coach will have a full roster. 
</P>
<P>
	They lost in the first round of the NCAA tournament last season  
and could face NCAA sanctions because of an academic fraud scandal 
that caused coach Clem Haskins' departure. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
