<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Three Tenors Play Only U.S. Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- The Three Tenors took center field at Tiger  
Stadium for their only North American engagement scheduled this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	About 35,000 people, wearing everything from silk dresses to  
khaki shorts, attended the concert Saturday at the 87-year-old 
building, which was transformed into an opera hall for the evening. 
</P>
<P>
	Jose Carreras, Placido Domingo and Luciano Pavarotti, who became  
known as The Three Tenors in 1990, first performed together at the 
World Cup in Rome. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
