<HEADLINE>  U.S. Arrives at Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GUADALAJARA, Mexico (AP) -- The U.S. team arrived Sunday for the  
FIFA Confederations Cup, and coach Bruce Arena acknowledged the 
Americans are a longshot. 
</P>
<P>
	Arena said he hoped to beat New Zealand on Saturday in the  
Americans' opener, but conceded the first-round games against 
Brazil (July 28) and Germany (July 30) would be difficult. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Americans are eliminated, Arena said Mexico would become  
his favorite to win the fourth edition of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Arena said the Americans would play an exhibition game this week  
against Egypt, which is in the tournament's other group. 
</P>
<P>
	The tournament is for the champions of each of soccer's  
continental confederations. France, the World Cup champion, was 
invited but declined. 
</P>
<P>
	The first three Conferations Cups were played in Saudi Arabia.  
  	   	
