<HEADLINE> White Sox' Thomas Leaves Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- White Sox first baseman Frank Thomas left  
Chicago's game with the Milwaukee Brewers in the first inning 
Sunday after suffering a bruised right foot. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas, who reached base after being hit by Bill Pulsipher, was  
leading off third base when Brook Fordyce fouled off a pitch. The 
line shot hit Thomas on his foot, and he fell hard to the ground. 
</P>
<P>
	He stayed in the game and later was forced out at the plate, but  
Paul Konerko replaced him at first base to start the bottom of the 
first inning. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas was taken to St. Michael Hospital for X-rays, which were  
negative. The team listed him as day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas is hitting .323 this season with 12 home runs, 25 doubles  
and 57 RBI. He has played in all 89 of Chicago's games, the only 
player to do so. 
  	   	
</P>
