<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CNN Beefing Up Financial Content </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- CNN is adding 2 1/2 hours of financial news on  
weekdays and giving Wolf Blitzer a prime-time anchor slot as part 
of a schedule overhaul to go into effect in September. 
</P>
<P>
	The news network will also change the time slot and format for  
its struggling newsmagazine series, ``NewsStand.'' 
</P>
<P>
	CNN will add ``Money Talks,'' a business-oriented breaking news  
program, from 11 a.m. to noon ET, replacing a talk show. ``Street 
Sweep,'' a half-hour wrapup of Wall Street activity, will air at 4 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	The one-hour business news program that now airs at 6 a.m. will  
double in length, starting at 5 a.m. to take advantage of growing 
early-morning TV viewership. All of the new business programming 
will be simulcast on CNNfn, the network's financial news sister 
station. 
</P>
<P>
	``Moneyline,'' a business wrapup that airs at 6:30 p.m., is  
CNN's most lucrative show. The additions are a reflection of the 
hunger for business news, said CNN USA President Rick Kaplan. 
</P>
<P>
	``The issues that are growing big-time are the pocketbook  
issues,'' he said. The expansion of business news does not, he 
said, mean trouble for CNNfn, which is the poor sister to CNBC in 
financial programming because of its inability to be picked up on 
many cable systems. 
</P>
<P>
	Blitzer, CNN's longtime White House correspondent, will anchor  
``The World Today'' newscast at 8 p.m. with the current anchors, 
Joie Chen and Jim Moret. The show shifts from 10 p.m. to 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	``NewsStand'' will move back to 10 p.m., where it launched last  
year. CNN said it will be more of a live news show and less of a 
newsmagazine, and will drop the nightly themes it used in 
collaboration with Time Inc. magazines. Willow Bay, Stephen Frazier 
and Judd Rose will share anchor roles. 
</P>
<P>
	``NewsStand'' has struggled in the ratings and saw its  
reputation hurt when it aired a report about alleged Vietnam War 
era nerve gas use that the network later retracted. 
</P>
<P>
	The new format will give CNN more flexibility to respond to  
breaking news yet still do the type of stories that appeared on the 
newsmagazine, Kaplan said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I really think the network needs, if you're a full-service  
network, to do more than breaking news,'' he said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
