inning, his teammates completely ignored him, in keeping with 
baseball superstitions. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of them had been through this when David Wells pitched his  
perfect game last season for the Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been spoiled by a couple perfect games, and I think that  
helped the mood,'' Yankees shortstop Derek Jeter said. 
</P>
<P>
	Outfielder and designated hitter Chili Davis was the only one  
who tried to lighten things up. 
</P>
<P>
	He was catching Cone during warmups in the eighth inning and  
told Cone to throw the ball faster. 
