<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Milton Berle Celebrates Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Uncle Miltie celebrated his 91st  
birthday surrounded at the Friars Club by fellow funnymen, his 
family and friends. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 300 people packed the comedy club for Milton Berle's  
celebration. Though he officially turned 91 on July 12, the party 
was put on hold until Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Berle was joined by his wife, Lorna, and their grandchildren. He  
was presented with a large, three-tier cake with chocolate, 
vanilla, strawberry and raspberry. It also had 91 candles. 
</P>
<P>
	Steve Allen, Larry King, Larry Miller and Eric Roberts were  
among the celebrities in attendance. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
