<HEADLINE> Martin Show Sells Out in 30 Mins. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- It took fans only 30 minutes to snap up all the  
tickets for Ricky Martin's Oct. 24 concert. 
</P>
<P>
	Even at $97 apiece, the best of the 15,000 seats at the new  
Philips Arena, which hasn't even opened yet, were the first to go 
when they went on sale Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ricky Martin,'' the first English-language CD from the  
27-year-old singer has had the best-ever album debut by a Hispanic 
artist on the mainstream Billboard charts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
